             sworn.</p>
               <p>I tied up the baskets.</p>
               <p>(Deposed to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17920912-77-person719">
                  JOSEPH
                   WHITEHEAD
               <interp inst="t17920912-77-person719" type="surname" value="WHITEHEAD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17920912-77-person719" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17920912-77-person719" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I believe this is a part of the hair I weighed in the evening of the 20th, for the prisoner; I have no doubt of it.</p>
               <p>PRISONER'S DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I bought these at Bristol myself; I can produce some more, and they cannot tell a difference.</p>
               <p>The prisoner called seven witnesses, who gave him a very good character.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17920912-77-verdict420" type="verdictDescription">
